==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brustle
<hw>Brus"tle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Brustled</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Brustling</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>brustlien</ets> and <ets>brastlien</ets>, AS. <ets>brastlian</ets>,
fr. <ets>berstan</ets> to burst, akin to G. <ets>prasseln</ets> to
crackle. See <er>Burst</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
crackle; to rustle, as a silk garment.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make a show of fierceness or defiance; to
bristle.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To brustle up</b></col>, <cd>to bristle up.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Otway.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brustle</ent>⟦br⟧

